(12, 5, 61, 'chilly-chicken-gravy', 'Chilly Chicken Gravy', 'Here goes the most easy &amp; delicious chilly chicken gravy recipe. In this recipe, boneless chicken cubes are marinated, fried and seasoned in spicy tangy sauces to get the best Indo-Chinese taste.', '<div class=\"post-module--postText--S050c\" style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-family:Rubik, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:21px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:-0.004em;line-height:1.58;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:pre-wrap;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing:inherit;margin:0px 0px 1.45rem;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Here goes the most easy &amp; delicious chilly chicken gravy recipe. In this recipe, boneless chicken cubes are marinated, fried and seasoned in spicy tangy sauces to get the best Indo-Chinese taste. It combines excellent with fried rice, chapatti, poori, roti and noodles. Try this popular recipe and enjoy the garlicky chilly luscious gravy recipe.</span></p></div><div style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);font-family:Rubik, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:medium;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;height:auto !important;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><div class=\"post-module--recipeMetaContainer--23nay\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;display:flex;flex-direction:row;margin-bottom:1.45em;\"><div style=\"box-sizing:inherit;\">&nbsp;</div></div><div class=\"post-module--ingredientsContainer--1XMrJ\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;margin-bottom:20px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:inherit;font-size:1.62671rem;line-height:1.1;margin:0px 0px 1.45rem;padding:0px;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;\"><span style=\"font-size:25px;\"><strong>Ingredients</strong></span></h2><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">To marinate:</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Boneless chicken - ½ kg</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Maida / all purpose flour - 3 tbsp</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Corn starch - 2 tbsp</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Soy sauce - 2 tsp</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Ginger garlic paste - 1 tbsp</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Vinegar -1 tsp</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Green chilly - 1</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Salt to taste</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\">&nbsp;</p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">To make Gravy:</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Onion - 2</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Green chilly - 2</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Capsicum chopped - ½ cup</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postListItem--1ohM9\" style=\"box-sizing:inherit;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);font-size:21px;letter-spacing:-0.004em;margin:0px 0px 8px;padding:0px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Oil - to deep fry</span></p><p class=\"post-module--postLi